1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) - The paper proposes a channel fusion method that improves the accuracy of neural networks, which is a common problem in computer vision tasks. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The proposed method involves learning parameters at training time, which is a key aspect of machine learning. 
3. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) - The paper deals with neural network architecture design and optimization, which falls under the scope of this sub-category. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The proposed method aims to improve the performance of neural networks, which is a key area of research in AI. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper introduces a new algorithmic technique, the Butterfly Transform, which is a variant of the Discrete Fourier Transform and has interesting properties that ensure the efficacy of the resulting network.
